# Greetings!

<a name="site-map"></a>

My name is **W. Caleb McDaniel**. I'm an assistant professor of history at Rice University and a scholar of the nineteenth-century United States. On this site you can find my **[publications][]**, occasional posts on my current **[research](./research.html)** and **[teaching](./teaching.html)**, and some geeky computer **[hacks](./hacks.html)**.

[![](./images/book.jpg)][Amazon] My first book, *The Problem of Democracy in the Age of Slavery: Garrisonian Abolitionists and Transatlantic Reform*, is forthcoming from [LSU Press][] in May 2013 ([Amazon][]). In the meantime, you can read [the introduction](./book-introduction.html). In AY 2012-2013 I am leading a [Masterclass on Digital History](http://digitalhistory.blogs.rice.edu). During the Spring 2013 semester I am teaching [HIST 118](http://hist118.wcaleb.rice.edu) and [HIST 588](http://wcm1.web.rice.edu/hist588spring13.pdf).

